<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Israeli Attacks on Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi strongly condemned Sunday the Israeli
bomb attacks on south Lebanon, which wounded two Lebanese
civilians.
</P>
<P>
Asefi said that the Israeli bombardments of south Lebanese
villages were "clear violation of the Lebanese sovereignty," the
Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He termed Tel Aviv as the main source of tension and
instability in the region, saying that measures taken by the
Israeli regime forced the region towards insecurity and tension.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian spokesman called for serious attention from the
international community and world public opinion to the issue of
Israel's "inhumane measures."
</P>
<P>
A Lebanese man and woman were wounded Sunday by shells fired by
Israeli forces.
</P>
<P>
The shelling came in retaliation for attacks launched by
Iranian-backed Hezbollah guerrilla on positions of Israeli troops
and the Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army (SLA).
</P>
<P>
The Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli occupation
troops and the SLA from south Lebanon, where Israel set up a
security zone in 1985 with the claim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
