<BODY>
<HEADLINE> URGENT: At Least 26 People Burned Dead in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 26 people died while
several others were injured and thousands rendered homeless in a
devastating fire Sunday afternoon in a slum cluster in northern
Delhi, police sources said here tonight.
</P>
<P>
However, unofficial sources said more than 30 people were
killed in the fire which broke out at 15:30 local time and is yet
to be brought under control.
</P>
<P>
Firemen recovered about 20 charred bodies from a mosque located
in the area, inhabited mostly by rag pickers and stocked with
inflammable material.
</P>
<P>
Plastic material and a strong breeze from the nearby Yamuna
River fanned the flames which within minutes destroyed hundreds of
huts and rendered thousands homeless.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said 10 companies of the city police in riot
gear moved into the area to assist the fire brigade which was
attacked by angry residents protesting alleged delay in reaching
the spot.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is yet to be ascertained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
