<HEADLINE> Nigerian President-Elect Winds Up Mozambique Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's President-elect Olusegun
Obasanjo ended his good-will blitz visit to Mozambique Sunday
afternoon and left for Kenya to continue his first visit after he
won in the Nigerian general elections.
</P>
<P>
Before ending his hours-long visit, Obasanjo said at a press
conference that his current visit was not an official visit, but a
good-will visit aimed at expressing his thanks to Mozambican
President Joaquim Chissano and other leaders who have offered him
support during and after the days when he was imprisoned.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian president-elect said that he wanted to use the
time before he take the office to visit some countries, so as to
get a better understanding of the domestic and regional situation,
as he had been kept away from politics and social life for a long
time.
</P>
<P>
Chissano said at the same occasion that Obasanjo has come to
Mozambique to see the situation here, so he could develop good
cooperation ties between Nigeria and Mozambique after he is
officially sworn in on May 29.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian president-elect came to Mozambique after his
two-day visit to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Obasanjo will also visit other countries
including Namibia, Japan, Britain, France, Germany and the United
States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
