<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Conduct Nationwide Survey on Human </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Central Statistical
Authority of Ethiopia announced Sunday that a nationwide manpower
survey aimed at gathering information on the number and
distribution of human resource across the nation will be conducted
as of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the authority as saying that
the seven- day survey will be conducted in 1,428 rural and 913
urban towns.
</P>
<P>
The authority said, information will be gathered from 35 sample
families in each selected locality and a total of more than 81,000
families across the nation will be contacted for the survey.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 statisticians and 1,488 data collectors will take
part in the survey and participants in the survey have been given
six to ten days of training, according to the authority.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has a total population of 59 million people, the third
largest in Africa following Nigeria and Egypt. Unemployment rate
in Ethiopian towns is about 30 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
