<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police Clashes With Separatists in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Yugoslavia, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav
police and troops clashed Sunday with armed separatists in
western Kosovo, killing four of the separatists.
</P>
<P>
The clash took place near Klina early in the day when some
armed separatists opened fire at the Yugoslav police and troops
with automatic weapons and grenade propelors.
</P>
<P>
The following exchange of fire killed four members of the
separatists who all wore the uniforms of the Kosovo Liberation
Army, according to military sources here in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In another development of the day, Zoran Andjelkovic, president
of the temporary executive council of the self-proclaimed republic
of Kosovo, described Saturday's bomb blasts as "the most violent
onslaught on the efforts to bring lasting peace to Kosovo."
</P>
<P>
He made the remark while visiting Sunday in the Pristina
hospital the wounded people of Saturday's three bomb blasts. He
urged bringing of the perpetrators of the bomb blasts to be
brought to justice.
</P>
<P>
A total of 31 injured were being treated in the Pristina
hospital, of whom 21 were brought in from Podujevo and the others
from Kosovska Mitrovica.
</P>
<P>
Two planted bombs went off at Podujevo and a third one blasted
at Kosovska Mitrovica Saturday afternoon, killing six people and
injuring dozens of others altogether. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
