<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Announces Fighting at Zalambessa-Egela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced that the
Ethiopian and Eritrean forces were fighting at Zalambessa-Egela
front Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Sunday night the Office of
Ethiopian Government Spokesperson Selome Taddesse as saying that
"there was fighting today on the Zalambessa-Egela front" between
the Ethiopian defense forces and the Eritrean army.
</P>
<P>
The one-sentence report did not disclose details of the
fighting.
</P>
<P>
Zalambessa-Egela front is located at eastern Tigray region.
Ethiopia accused the Eritrean forces of occupying the border town
Zalambessa on June 9, last year.
</P>
<P>
The Office of Ethiopian Government Spokesperson said in a
statement issued recently that "although the liberation of Badme
was an important achievement, it must not be forgotten that
thousands of Ethiopians continue to endure Eritrean occupation and
that sovereign Ethiopian territory still remains in Eritrean
hands."
</P>
<P>
The Office accused that the Eritrean forces continue to occupy
Ethiopian territories in the Zalambessa-Aiga region, Egela region
and Bada-Bure region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
