<HEADLINE> Nigeria President-Elect Visits Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's President-elect
Olusegun Obasanjo arrived in Kenya Sunday evening from Mozambique
to start a two-day official visit to this east African nation.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi met the Nigerian leader at
Nairobi Jomo Kenyatta International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Kenya is Obasanjo's fourth leg of his month-long foreign tour
since his election last month. He had visited Benin, Tanzania and
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that Obasanjo will address Kenyan businessmen and
meet senior government officials Monday.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo will also visit some Asian and European countries as
well the United States. 
</P>
