<HEADLINE> Syrian, U.S. Officials Meet Over Regional Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq
Sharaa and visiting U.S. Assistant Secretary of State for Mideast
Affairs Martin Indyk met here on Sunday over the stalled Mideast
peace process and the U.S.-Syrian relations.
</P>
<P>
After his talks with Sharaa, Indyk also said that he had
discussed with Sharaa the situation in South Lebanon and the need
to guarantee tanquility in the region, among other issues.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Iraq was also one the topics of their talks,
Indyk said. Syrian President Hafez Assad on Sunday evening also
met with Martin Indyk.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival from Amman on Saturday, Indyk said he came
here for consultations with Syrian officials "prompted by our
conviction of Syria's important role in the region." 
</P>
