<HEADLINE> Zambia's Cement Industry Earns More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA , March 14 (Xinhua) -- Cement production earned Zambia
62.53 billion kwacha (over 28.4 million U.S. dollars) with a net
profit of 14.283 billion kwacha (about 6.5 million dollars at
current rate) in 1998 compared with a net profit of 8.089 billion
Kwacha (about 3.7 million dollars) in 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to Chilanga Cement Corporation, overall domestic
sales increased by 1.6 percent in 1998 over 1997, the Zambian News
Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 the domestic sale stood at 242,057 tons.
</P>
<P>
Export fell by 29.3 percent in 1998, to 103,400 tons, with
Malawi, Burundi and the Democratic Republic of Congo being the
main destinations, whose imports accounted for over 95 percent of
Zambia's total cement exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
