<HEADLINE> Zambian Ruling Party Officials Criticized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- National Secretary of Zambia's
ruling party Michael Sata Sunday criticized the cadres of the
ruling Movement for Multi- Party Democracy (MMD) for going round
scandalizing the leadership of the party because of frustration.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency quoted Sata as saying that such cadres
are the root cause of the weaknesses the party is experiencing.
</P>
<P>
Addressing MMD district officials in Ndola, northern Zambia, he
said that such people are not worthy belonging to the party.
</P>
<P>
He told them that MMD has no room for rumor mongers and people
wishing to join it for personal gain.
</P>
<P>
He charged that most leaders including those at grass roots
level have failed to go round to explain to the people the
achievements of the MMD government including problems it has
encountered such as severe drought and heavy rainfall which has
destroyed crops.
</P>
<P>
Instead of going to the people to explain what the government
is doing they are in the forefront complaining just because they
have been frustrated, Sata said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
