<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, March 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The 4th International Defense Exhibition
(IDEX '99) was inaugurated here on Sunday by Crown Prince Sheike
Khalifa, deputy supreme commander of the armed forces of the
United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
Present at the opening ceremony were defense officials from the
UAE, Kuwait, Oman, Italy, South Africa, Britain, the U.S., France,
Russia, etc. (BC-UAE-Defense Show)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The warring parties in Afghanistan on Sunday reached
a landmark agreement in Turkmenistan's capital Ashkhabad on a
shared government, exchange of prisoners of war and continuation
of peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached between representatives of the
ruling Taliban militia and the opposition coalition based in
northern Afghanistan in their four-day peace talks which opened
Thursday under the auspice of the United Nations.(BC-Iran-Afghan
Talks)
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Foreign Minister of the United Arab Emirates
(UAE) Rashid Bin Abdullah Al-Nuaimi reiterated his country's
rejection to Iran's recent actions on three disputed Gulf islands.
</P>
<P>
"The provocative and unjustified Iranian conducts pose a
danger to the region, threaten to cause instability and do not
serve the good neighborly ties between Iran and the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC) states," Al-Nuaimi said at the opening
session of the GCC foreign ministerial meeting in Saudi capital
Riyadh Sunday. (BC-UAE-Iran-Islands)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- U.S. and British warplanes Sunday continued to bomb
civilian facilities and military sites in northern and southern
Iraq, an Iraqi military spokesman announced.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency quoted the unnamed spokesman as saying
that at 8:50 a.m. (0550 GMT), 32 formations of U.S.-British
warplanes from Saudi and Kuwaiti bases violated southern Iraqi
airspace over Dhi-Qar, Najaf, Muthana and Basra
provinces. (BC-Iraq-US Raids)


14/03/99 20:57 GMT

NNNN
05:00 05:00 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
