<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 14 (Xinhua ) -- The following are economic briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
MUSCAT -- DAEWOO, South Korean Construction and Engineering
Works Corporation offered 25 million Omani Rial (64 million
U.S. dollars) to lay down an offshore wave-break under the Omani
Suhar harbor renovation project.
</P>
<P>
The Arabic daily Al-Alam Al-Youm reported Sunday that Suhar
harbor renovation project comprises building a wave-break of 5-6
kilometers long in two years and a new quay.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Three cement production lines are expected to be
installed in Egypt by June to raise the country's annual cement
production to 25 million tonnes at the value of 5 billion Egyptian
pounds (1.47 billion dollars), the Al-Alam Al-Youm reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
MANAMA -- Bahraini Finance and National Economy Ministry said
it inked a contract with the Jeddah-based Islamic Development Bank
to get a 34.3 million dollars loan.
</P>
<P>
The fresh loan will be used in financing an 80-million-dollar
project designed to import and install equipments of six power
plants.
</P>
<P>
RABAT -- The Moroccan Potable Water National Bureau said the
Islamic Development Bank has decided to provide it with 273
million Drihams (29 million dollars) in loans to fund several
projects in the southern province of Taza .
</P>
<P>
The Arabic daily Al-Haiyat reported Sunday Taza, which is
getting water supplies from an underground water layer, suffers
shortage of potable water specially in dry seasons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
