<HEADLINE> South Asian Foreign Secretaries Meet in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Foreign secretaries from South
Asian countries met in the Sri Lankan central town of Nuwara Eliya
to discuss mutual issues ahead of a meeting of regional foreign
ministers later this week, a government statement said Monday
night.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the foreign secretaries met Monday afternoon
for the 26th session of the Standing Committee of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC).
</P>
<P>
The meeting will review the progress in the implementation of
the South Asia Preferential Trade Arrangement, several SAARC
conventions and cooperation with international and regional
organizations among others.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the 21st session of the Programming Committee at the
Senior Officials' level, which commenced deliberations Saturday,
concluded its session Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the SAARC will meet in Nuwara Eliya on
March 18-19 for the 21st session of the Council of Ministers, to
discuss economic issues, including plans to set up a free trade
area.
</P>
<P>
SAARC groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Nepal, the Maldives,
Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
