<HEADLINE> Clash Near Pristina As Peace Talks Resume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Yugoslavia, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Clashes
picked up again on Monday around Pristina as peace talks resumed
in Paris trying to bring peace back to the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
Beatrice Lacoste, spokesperson of the Kosovo Verification
Mission from the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE), said there was fighting in the village of Lebane at
around high noon.
</P>
<P>
Lebane is within 20 minutes by car from the provincial capital,
where the press rushed only to see seven tanks and six armored
vehicles perching by the road and five truck loads of troops of
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia were sent in as reinforcement.
</P>
<P>
The Pristina Media Center told the press that heavily-armed
separatists attacked the police station and Yugoslav army units
around Lebane and Luzane overnight with automatic weapons.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav security forces returned fire and the fight lasted
from late Sunday night till early Monday morning, the Yugoslav
government information service said.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported from the government side.
</P>
<P>
In the past few days, as the continuation of the Kosovo peace
talks drew near, violent events like bomb blasts and arsenal
attacks increased, especially in northern and western Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday alone, clashes between Yugoslav forces and armed
separatists claimed the lives of at least 10 people in western
Kosovo, according to a press officer with the Kosovo Verification
Mission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
