<HEADLINE> Chinese And Japanese Airlines Sharing Flight Codes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Airlines and All
Nippon Airways (ANA) announced a code-sharing agreement here today
to use China Eastern's flight codes on ANA's Shanghai-Osaka and
Beijing-Qingtao-Osaka flights and ANA's flight codes on China
Eastern's similar flights.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern, one of the nation's largest airlines, has more
than 30 flights each week to Japan and ANA has more than 50 to
China. The code-sharing will automatically double the two airlines'
flights between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
A China Eastern executive says that the airline expects to open
a route to Japan's Fukushima.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern is also sharing codes with more than ten world
airlines, including American Airlines, Korean Airlines, and Asiana
Airlines.  
</P>
