<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Children Hard Hit by Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 14,200 children
were raped in South Africa in the first 11 months of 1998, or 43
children a day, police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rape figure had almost doubled since 1994, when about 7,500
cases were reported, according to figures released at a police
conference on crimes against children.
</P>
<P>
Another 3,450 children were indecently assaulted, and 1,100
were kidnapped, the figures showed.
</P>
<P>
Overall, more than 33,000 crimes against people under 18 were
recorded during the 11 months.
</P>
<P>
Police said they are training police social workers who could
assess children victims by therapeutic techniques, which enabled
them to give vital testimony to help convict the accused in sexual
offenses against children.
</P>
<P>
In the past, some of the accused were released because the
traumatized children could not provide sufficient evidence for a
conviction, police said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
