<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails Success of NPC Session (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Tuesday issue of the People's
Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial marking
the successful conclusion of the Second Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, titled "Be united as one and make pragmatic
efforts to invigorate the country", describes the just-concluded
NPC session as a "democratic, united, truth-seeking and inspiring"
meeting.
</P>
<P>
With a high sense of responsibility for the people and the
nation, the nearly 3,000 NPC deputies attending the session
examined a Government Work Report and a draft amendment to China's
Constitution, deliberated and approved the 1999 plan for China's
economic and social development and the 1999 budgets, and examined
other important reports and draft laws, says the editorial.
</P>
<P>
"They have made active efforts to ensure the success of the
work in various fields this year and to further promote the
country's economic growth and social progress," it adds.
</P>
<P>
The editorial points to the fact that the Constitutional
amendment adopted by the NPC session has endorsed Deng Xiaoping
Theory as China's guiding ideology, enshrined the principle of "
governing the country according to law", and defined the country's
fundamental economic and distribution systems, thus turning the
guidelines of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) into the will of the state through the legal procedure.
</P>
<P>
"This is in keeping with the aspirations of people of all
ethnic groups across the country and with our country's
fundamental situation of being at the primary stage of socialism,
which will last for a long period of time," the editorial says,
adding that the amendment also represents the biggest success for
the principle of "seeking truth from facts."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
