<HEADLINE> Ethnic Albanians Express Willingness to Sign Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethnic Albanians from Kosovo on
Monday expressed their willingness to sign a peace deal with
Yugoslavia in the second round of talks in the chateau of
Rambouillet outside Paris.
</P>
<P>
A French Foreign Ministry statement said head of the ethnic
Albanian delegation, Hashim Thaci had sent a letter to the co-
presidents of the conference, British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook
and French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
Thaci said in the letter that they are "ready to sign" an
international peace plan giving them broad political autonomy for
the next three years but keeping the Yugoslav province within the
borders of Serbia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
