<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Northwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake with a 5.6
magnitude hit the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region on 18:42
Beijing time today.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities are still looking into the extent of the
damage.
</P>
<P>
The China Seismology Bureau says that it occurred in an area
between Kuqa and Baicheng counties.
</P>
<P>
Strong shocks were felt in Baicheng, Kuqa, and Xinhe counties,
local authorities report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
