<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Indonesia Agree to Enhance Military Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Indonesia
Monday agreed that their close military ties should be further
enhanced despite the economic slowdown, Deputy Defense Minister
Abdullah Fadzil Che Wan said.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Fadzil met here Monday with visiting Indonesian Air
Force Chief Hanafie Asnan who is on a two-day visit, according to
the Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister said that they discussed the existing
military ties and appreciated the close military ties between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Military programs between the two countries should only be
those which do not incur large expenses, like exchange of officers
and courses conducted for officers of both countries, Bernama
quoted Abdullah Fadzil as saying.
</P>
<P>
Hanafie also called on his Malaysian counterpart Ahmad Saruji
Che Rose and Army Chief Mohamed Zahidi Zainuddin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
