<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK, Guangdong Cooperate in sustainable development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gordon Siu, Secretary for Planning, Environment and Lands of
the Special Administrative Region (SAR), made the remarks when
speaking at a seminar entitled "Hong Kong - Guangdong
Environmental Partnership, Seminar on Environment and Energy"
organized by the Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
He said sustainable development is a process that puts the
achievement of economic prosperity, social justice and
environmental quality on an equal footing, not deferring or
subordinating one in order to achieve another.
</P>
<P>
"It also requires understanding of the need to use resources
wisely so we don't prejudice the prospects of our children or
neighbors," he said. "It is not a goal Hong Kong and Guangdong
can each pursue in isolation, it is something we have to work
together to achieve."
</P>
<P>
Siu noted that communication is one of the essential ways to
achieve this target. "We shall build on the foundation laid by
meetings of the Hong Kong Guangdong Joint Co-operation Committee
and the Hong Kong-Guangdong Environmental Protection Liaison Group,
" he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
