<HEADLINE> UN Human Rights Official to Visit Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Kamal Hossain of the United
Nations Commission of Human Rights, as special rapporteur on the
situation of human rights in Afghanistan, will visit Afghanistan
and Pakistan from March 15 to 20.
</P>
<P>
The visit is being undertaken in the context of the special
rapporteur's mandate by virtue of a resolution of the Human Rights
Commission, said a press release issued here Monday by the U.N.
Office for Coordination of Humanitarian Assistance to Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with that resolution, the special rapporteur will
submit a report on the situation of human rights in Afghanistan to
the Commission on Human Rights at its 55th session in April, the
release said.
</P>
<P>
This is Hossain's first visit to Afghanistan as special
rapporteur, the release said. He will meet various officials in
Kabul as well as staff of the United Nations and non-governmental
organizations.
</P>
<P>
He will also hold discussions with officials of the Foreign
Office of Pakistan as well as refugees and other groups in
Peshawar, capital city of Pakistan's North West Frontier Province,
the release said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
