<HEADLINE> China's Everbright Bank Doing Well As Joint-Stock Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Everbright Bank of China (EBC)
has had rapid growth since it became a joint-stock bank in early
1997, sources close to the bank say.
</P>
<P>
Everbright was founded in 1992 and has 18 branches and more
than 100 offices across China and more than 700 offices in 65
countries and regions. At the end of 1998, its total assets
amounted to 74.7 billion yuan, net capital to 6.1 billion yuan,
and savings deposits amounted to 49.3 billion yuan,
</P>
<P>
EBC is tied to China Everbright Holding Co. Ltd. as a holding
company. Other major stockholders include the Asian Development
Bank, China Tobacco Corporation's Yunnan branch, and China
Construction Group Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Observers attribute the sustained growth of EBC to its
operations and comprehensive supervision system that exercises
strict control over loans and liabilities. It has attempted to
expand its business by shifting loans to state-backed
infrastructure construction and enterprises with a good record.
</P>
<P>
The bank has committed itself to providing round-the-clock
service to customers and by the second quarter of this year will
issue a new credit card, sources say.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
