<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Consumers More Aware of Their Rights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhang wasn't the first person to arrive. Government industrial
and commercial department and manufacturers' representatives had
already been there for quite some time to talk with people.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jianhua, A CCA official told reporters that since 1987
when China joined the International Consumers' Association,
government departments have held various activities on Consumer's
Day every year for publicity and information on consumer laws and
regulations and on specific cases.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that this year's theme is "safe and healthy consuming
" and that similar activities are being held today in other parts
of China.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen, with consumer awareness of the law gradually
increasing, consumer complaints have changed. They used to focus
on the inferior quality of daily necessities and food and drinks
but now the number of complaints about bad service, housing, and
medical care are on the rise.
</P>
<P>
There were more than 5 million people who used the law to
protect their rights last year and 1.52 billion yuan (183 million
US dollars) in losses was recovered.
</P>
</TEXT>
