<HEADLINE> Forest Fire Raging in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Forest fires are raging in
about nine districts of Nepal and two people have been reportedly
killed, officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fire has gutted 50 hectares of forest in Ilam and neighboring
Panchthar district in eastern Nepal, and two people were
reportedly killed, a district forest officer in Ilam said.
</P>
<P>
He said the fire spread to Ilam from Panchthar, which broke out
last Friday and had destroyed the Chintap National Forest in Ilam.
</P>
<P>
He said the fire was expected to be controlled within a few
days as 250 people were fighting it.
</P>
<P>
Four forests in Panchthar were burning but no one was killed, a
district administration officer said.
</P>
<P>
In Manang district of western Nepal, fire was engulfing some
seven hectares of forest and it was burning louder.
</P>
<P>
A district administration officer said that the fire has been
raging for the past 10 days and there is no possibility of putting
it out as the burning area is mountainous.
</P>
<P>
He said the army and police were trying to save the telephone
tower.
</P>
<P>
Nepal is in the period of dry season for months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
