<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 80.90 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday gained 80.90 points to
3,783.71 as against the previous close of 3,702.81.
</P>
<P>
The national index also gained by 40.55 points to 1,659.63 as
against the previous close of 1,619.08.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted higher at 380.45
and 149.32 compared with the last close of 372.26 and 146.07
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Software scrips were again in the forefront leading to a fresh
rally in equity prices at the BSE market Monday on heavy bull
support by foreign funds and speculators.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the stock market has entered the bull phase
on account of calm prevailing at the center and is attracting
foreign investors. 
