<HEADLINE> Financial Package Launched for SMIs in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Public Bank Bhd
Monday announced the launching of a special financial package to
promote lending under its Fund for Small and Medium Industries
(FSMI).
</P>
<P>
The FSMI package, to be available at all Public Bank's 177
branches nationwide, is valid for a one-month period for all SMI
loan applications received from March 16 to April 15, 1999, the
bank said in a statement Monday.
</P>
<P>
The package is launched in conjunction with the national
campaign for the "Promotion of SMI Funds" which will be held from
March 16-18 here, the bank said, adding the package is aimed at
making SMIs more accessible to financing.
</P>
<P>
The bank said all viable SMIs which comply with the FSMI
criteria for financing are eligible for this special package.
</P>
<P>
The features of the FSMI include financing in the form of term
loans and trade bills up to 200 percent of the value of acceptable
collaterals, financing of up to one million ringgit (263,000 U.S.
dollars) for qualified SMIs, a preferential interest rate of eight
percent per annum for secured facilities and quick access to the
fund where the bank would consider early partial disbursement
pending completion of security documentation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
