<HEADLINE> Japan Funding, Technology Co-operation Symposium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on Japanese
assistance to China and technological co-operation with China,
sponsored by China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation and Ministry of Science and Technology, the Japanese
Embassy in China, and the Japan International Co-operation Agency,
opened in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Government officials, scholars, and company representatives
from China and Japan discussed policies and strategy for funding
and technological co-operation and project management. The
participants said that funding should be connected to
technological co-operation more closely to ensure that projects
are more efficient.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, Japan had provided 158 billion yuan in
government loans to China, 8.1 billion yuan in free assistance,
and 7.6 billion yuan in financing for technological co-operation,
mainly for infrastructure, agriculture, environmental protection,
medical care, and health, education, and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Japanese government has been shifting
assistance to China's central and western parts for poverty relief.
</P>
</TEXT>
