<HEADLINE> Vietnam Proposes More Barter Trade With ASEAN, CIS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Trade Ministry has asked
Prime Minister Phan Van Khai to allow local businesses to barter
goods with ASEAN countries and the Commonwealth of Independent
States (CIS)to promoted exports this year, official media here
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The export items would include mechanical products,
handicrafts, rubber, electrical-electronic appliances, garments,
footwear, pharmaceuticals, salt, seafood, meat, milk and animal
products as well as other agricultural products, excluding rice
and coffee.
</P>
<P>
These would be bartered for motorbike components, fertilizers,
steel, clinker, ashlartiles and sanitary ware, construction glass
and electric fans.
</P>
<P>
An official with the ministry's Import-Export Division said
barter trade would promote exports to countries which had become
major markets for Vietnam in the last five years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, exports to these markets slumped due to the regional
economic crisis and the financial turmoil in the CIS.
</P>
<P>
Exports of pork to Russia came to a standstill last year. In
early 1998, Vietnam signed a contract to supply Russia with 2.5
million tons of pork. However, only a few thousand tons were
actually delivered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
