<HEADLINE> Inmates Riot at Malaysia's Drug Rehabilitation Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Some 490 inmates at a drug
rehabilitation center in Malaysia's eastern state of Pahang rioted
Monday, causing injuries to a policeman, the Malaysian national
news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
The policeman was hit by stones hurled by the inmates during
the riot, the second in five days, Bernama quoted the Pahang
police chief as saying.
</P>
<P>
The inmates went on a rampage, smashing vehicles of the
center's staff and breaking into quarters from where they took
some choppers, the police official said.
</P>
<P>
They rioted to vent their anger at the center's administration
for taking action against inmates who were caught leaving the
center without permission, the police official said.
</P>
<P>
The situation has been brought under control and 42 General
Operations Force troops and 15 Light Strike Force personnel were
deployed at the center, the official said.
</P>
<P>
According to Bernama, 10 inmates will be charged in court soon
in connection with the first rioting which happened on Thursday.
</P>
