<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host Pesticides Forum for Food Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Japanese and Filipino agricultural
experts will take up the latest global trends on the safe use of
pesticides at a forum Tuesday in line with the Philippines
government's goal of training rural folk on environment-friendly
ways of boosting farm productivity.
</P>
<P>
Two agencies attached to the Department of Agriculture (DA) -
the Fertilizer and Pesticide Authority (FPA) and the Bureau of
Plant Industry (BPI) -- are hosting a symposium entitled
"Emboldening the Safe Use of Pesticides toward Food Security in
the New Millennium."
</P>
<P>
The forum, a joint project of the FPA and BPI with the Japan
International Cooperation Agency (JICA), will be held at the
National Pesticide Analytical Laboratory in Manila.
</P>
<P>
The FPA said the forum will be attended by local pesticide
experts, members of the academe, farmer-representatives, industry
practitioners and other concerned groups.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the FPA launched a nationwide training program on the
latest agri-technologies in crop protection and balanced
fertilization as a way to raise the yields of small farmers while
cutting their production costs and environmental risks.
</P>
<P>
The FPA said that under the training project, "the trained
farmers will become trainers themselves to facilitate the transfer
of basic and appropriate agri-technologies in crop protection and
balanced fertilization, particularly rapid composting and soil
testing." 
</P>
