<HEADLINE> Central Socialist Academy Opens Spring Semester </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Non-Communist party officials,
who will study in the spring semester class of the Central
Socialist Academy, were urged today to improve their political
awareness and help their parties do a better job in participating
in government and political affairs.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the academy's spring
semester in Beijing today, Wang Zhaoguo, vice chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, called on the students to unite their party members to
gather around the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee
with Jiang Zemin at the core, hold high the banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory, share weal and woe with the CPC, and contribute
to the building of socialism with Chinese characteristics in the
21st Century.
</P>
<P>
The Central Socialist Academy is a united party school of non-
Communist parties and persons without party affiliation. He Luli,
vice chairwoman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress and chairman of the Revolutionary Committee of the
Chinese Kuomintang Central Committee, is the president of the
academy.
</P>
<P>
Some 127 officials, most of whom were newly elected for the new
term, will study there during the spring semester.
</P>
<P>
"We should strengthen our resolve to the leadership of the CPC
to seize opportunities and face challenges of the new century,"
concluded Wang Zhaoguo, also head of the United Front Work
Department of the CPC Central Committee. 
</P>
