<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Uses Past Experience To Ease Financial Crisis Impact: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
here today that the reason for China to stand "rock firm" amid the
Asian financial crisis is that it prevented the country from an
overheated economy by implementing proper macro-economic
regulation and control.
</P>
<P>
"As a matter of fact, China experienced such crisis as early as
in 1993. Fortunately we took measures to check the unhealthy trend
timely before it got spread," said the premier at the press
conference this afternoon held immediately after the closing
meeting of the 2nd session of the National People's Congress,
China's highest lawmaking body.
</P>
<P>
Looking back at the economic overheating in 1993 in sectors of
real estate, development zones and stock market which led to an
inflation rate of 21.7 percent in 1994, Zhu said that of the 16
macro-economic regulation measures the central government took to
fight the runaway inflation, 13 are economic measures, out of
which 11 were related to banking and financial sectors.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the measures, China has brought its economy back onto
the right track and resumed its growth momentum and has scored
great achievements since then, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He cited a New York Times article which criticized the United
States for its role in prompting the financial crisis in Asia,
stressing that economic development and financial liberalization
must be accompanied with macro control and regulation policies and
different macro control or regulation polices should be adopted
according to the specific conditions of different countries, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"To urge a country to liberalize or open its capital market too
quickly, or to require an overflow of capital in the country would
only result in what we say 'more haste, less speed' and can only
undermine the economy of the country concerned," Zhu warned.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
