<HEADLINE> EDS-URGENT China's Premier Vows to Further Open Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China's Premier Zhu Rongji said
here today that China will further open its telecommunications
market to foreign investors and open renminbi business to more
foreign banks in China.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the pledge at a press conference this afternoon, which
was held right after the conclusion of the Second Session of the
Ninth National People's Congress, the nation's top legislature.
</P>
<P>
Although he did not provide any details concerning market-
opening, the Premier said it is a general principle to further
open the market.
</P>
<P>
He suggested Hong Kong bankers to apply for setting up branches
in China as early as possible, saying "the earlier you apply, the
sooner you will get approved."
</P>
<P>
Zhu also vowed to reform the system of the telecommunications
industry, break monopoly and introduce competition into the
telecommunications market.
</P>
<P>
He stressed China will cut down the level of charges on
telecommunication services "continuously and by several times".
</P>
