<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Consumer Price Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Consumer Price
Index (CPI) for February this year rose 3.8 percent compared with
the same month of 1998, the Statistics Department said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The CPI for February this year, which stood at 118.6 points,
was 0.2 percent higher that a year earlier, due to increases in
indexes in five main groups -- food, gross rent, fuel and power,
transport and communication, medical care and health expenses, and
furniture, furnishings &AMP; household equipment and operation, the
department said.
</P>
<P>
The CPI for January-February 1999 was up 4.5 percent at 118.5
points, compared with the 113.4 points a year earlier, due to
increases in the indexes of seven main groups -- Food, beverages
and tobacco, medical care and health expenses, recreation,
entertainment, education &AMP; cultural services, furniture,
furnishings &AMP; household equipment and operation, miscellaneous
goods &AMP; services, and gross rent, fuel &AMP; power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
