<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar drifted
lower Monday through the course of the day and accelerated its
losses into the close.
</P>
<P>
The currency was unable to get on board Friday's rally in the
Japanese yen while last week's support from commodity price gains
also waned.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar traversed a muted range, struggling to a
high at 63.61 U.S. cents in opening business only to be trading at
its lows at 63.32 U.S. cents as local traders signed off the day.
</P>
<P>
At the close in Sydney, the local currency was traded at 63.32
U.S. cents from 63.42 U.S. cents at Friday's close.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was also buying 0.5750 euro from 0.5749
euro at Friday's close and 75.06 Japanese yen from 75.52 yen.
