<HEADLINE> Police Leave Canceled for 2000 New Year in Australian States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- All police leave over 2000 New
Year has been canceled in Australia's southeastern state of
Tasmania because of fears of huge parties and Y2K (year 2000
millennium bug) problems.
</P>
<P>
Tasmania is believed to be the second state to have cancelled
all police leave after Victoria.
</P>
<P>
The Tasmania state government decided Monday that all police
leave between December 28, 1999 and January 14, 2000 be cancelled,
according to an Australian Associated Press report.
</P>
<P>
Southeastern Tasmania, which will be one of the first parts of
Australia to see the dawn of the new millennium, is expecting huge
New Years Eve parties.
</P>
<P>
Most hotels in the capital city Hobart, are already booked out.
</P>
<P>
Although the government believes it's well advanced in dealing
with millennium bug problems, it's taking no chances.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman said extra police would be needed in case vital
facilities like traffic lights crashed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
