<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator on Role of NPC-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Second Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress, which just successfully concluded, has
been a democratic, united, pragmatic and inspiring conference,
said Li Peng, China's top legislator here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the closing meeting of the current session of the
Ninth NPC, the nation's highest legislature, Li Peng said, "China
faces even more arduous tasks this year given the new situations
and new problems in its economic and social development."
</P>
<P>
"We hope the State Council and the ministries and departments
concerned could improve work by earnestly studying the proposals
and suggestions raised by the NPC deputies and the resolutions
adopted at the current session," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li also called for efforts to promote reform and opening-up,
expand domestic demand, further state-owned enterprise reform,
ensure survival stipends and re-employment of laid-off workers,
and build a clean and efficient government, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to judicial corruption as a problem of common concern
among the deputies, the Ninth NPC Standing Committee chairman
pointed out that a basic solution is to further judicial reform
and improve the supervisory system to ensure just jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng also spoke highly of constitutional amendments in his
speech. He said the NPC session amends the Constitution at an
appropriate time and in accordance with the guidelines of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Li noted the amendment endorses Deng Xiaoping as a guiding
ideology of China, enshrines the principle of "governing the
country according to law", defines the country's fundamental
economic and distribution systems in the current stage and
highlights the important role of the non-public sector in the
national economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
