<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator on Role of NPC-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Affirming the status of the Chinese Communist Party as the core
of the leadership of the nation's socialist cause and the ruling
party of the country, the top legislator said that consolidating
the Party's leadership conforms to giving play to the role of the
people's congresses.
</P>
<P>
"Under the leadership of the Party, the people draw up the
Constitution and law, abide by and enforce the Constitution and
law. The Party also carries out its activities within the
framework of the Constitution and law." he said.
</P>
<P>
"Compared to its legislative work, the supervisory role of the
people's congresses is still a weak link and such role needs to be
improved and strengthened," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"Supervision should be strengthened on key issues concerning
reform, development, and stability, problems of common concern,
and problems which attract the loudest complaints from the general
public." Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said the NPC Standing Committee has set on its legislation
agenda the drafting of Law of Supervision and will work it out as
early as possible in response to the call of the NPC deputies at
the session.
</P>
<P>
The chairman also called for the people's congresses and their
standing committees to follow the mass line in legislation and
supervision.
</P>
<P>
"All the power of the state belongs to the people, and the
people exercise the state power through the National People's
Congress and local people's congresses. The people empower the
people's congresses, and the people's congresses should take it
their responsibilities to exercise the power on people's behalf,"
he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
