<HEADLINE> First Boxing Bar Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A boxing bar, the first if its
kind, opened recently on the east side of Beijing, and business
there has been very good.
</P>
<P>
The bar, called the Bason Club, is nearly 100 square meters in
size and can hold about 200 guests at a time. What makes it rather
special is the 30-square-meter boxing ring in the center of the
bar, which enables guests to enjoy exciting boxing matches while
drinking their red wine.
</P>
<P>
Tan Jingsheng, the bar's deputy general manager, said that
boxing has become more and more popular in China over the past few
years, and many folks like to watch boxing in their leisure time,
so they decided to open a bar where they could do just that. They
aim to combine the relaxing atmosphere of a bar with the exciting
sport of boxing to provide their guests with all-round
entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The boxers are from both professionals and amateurs, and the
fans including students, businessmen, and company staffs also have
shown great interest in boxing training classes there.
</P>
<P>
"I just love the place. I can chat with my friends here, and at
the same time we enjoy ourselves by watching exciting boxing,"
said Lin Li, an actress who often invites her friends to the bar.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
