<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Session of Ninth NPC Ends (Details)-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Second Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC), which opened on March 5, came to
an end at the Great Hall of the People here this afternoon, with
all the items on the agenda well completed and a number of
resolutions adopted.
</P>
<P>
NPC Standing Committee Chairman Li Peng presided over the
closing meeting of the session, which was attended by Chinese
Party and state leaders Jiang Zemin, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu
Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing as well as 2,866 NPC deputies.
</P>
<P>
During the 11-day session, the deputies examined the government
work report, the report on the implementation of 1998 plan for
national economic and social development and the report on the
proposed plan for national economic and social development in 1999,
the report on the 1998 implementation of central and local budgets
and the report on the proposed central and local budgets for 1999.
</P>
<P>
The three reports were earnestly examined over the past few
days and three resolutions on the reports were separately adopted
and approved at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
The deputies voted by secret ballots to pass an amendment to
the Constitution, and according to the amendment, the position of
the guiding ideology of Deng Xiaoping Theory, the basic principle
of governing the country according to law, the basic economic and
distribution systems at the current stage of the country and the
important role of the non-public economic sector, were added into
the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
This is the third partial revision on the Constitution adopted
in 1982, following the previous the revisions in 1988 and 1993
respectively.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting, the Law of the People's Republic of China
on Contracts, the first unified contract law in China, and the
Methods for Selecting Deputies of the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) to the Ninth National People's Congress were also
adopted.
</P>
<P>
The new contract law, which has 23 chapters in 428 articles, is
scheduled to be promulgated on October 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to the Methods, the number of NPC deputies from the
Macao SAR is 12, including the present five Macao NPC deputies
elected at the Ninth Guangdong Provincial People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Three resolutions were also passed separately at today's
meeting, approving the work reports by the NPC Standing Committee,
the People's Supreme Court and the People's Supreme Procuratorate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Session of Ninth NPC Ends (Details)-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the closing meeting of the current session, NPC
Standing Committee Chairman Li Peng said that the resolutions and
laws adopted at the session is a complete reflection of the
fundamental interests and the will and aspirations of the people.
He called it a democratic, united, pragmatic and inspiring
conference, urging people to advance.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed: "All the state power belongs to the people, and
the people exercise the state power through the National People's
Congress and local people's congresses. The people empower the
people's congresses, and the people's congresses should regard it
their obligations to exercise the power on behalf of the people."
</P>
<P>
He urged the people's congresses at different levels to keep
lose ties with the people, depend on them, look into their
situation, express their will and pull together their talent and
wisdom, this is the basis for the work of the people's congresses
and the source of the vitality of the work of the people's
congresses, he added.
</P>
<P>
The legislative and supervisory work of the NPC and its
Standing Committee should be carried out by following the mass
line, the NPC leader said. The formulations and revisions of laws
must be based on the Constitution, centering on the general
interests of the state and representing the fundamental interests
of the people, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the drafts of important laws should be made public
and seek opinions and suggestions from the public.
</P>
<P>
The legal supervision should be combined with the supervision
by the people and the media, he said, urging the media to increase
their coverage on building democracy and the legal system and the
work of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
In conclusion, Li Peng said that the year 1999 is a year of
special significance in the history of China's development. He
called on all the deputies, upon returning to their respective
posts, to earnestly publicize and implement the guidelines of the
session, mobilize and unite with the people to do their work
better, and greet the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic and the return of Macao with outstanding
achievements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
