<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Iron, Steel Prices Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China's iron and steel prices are
remaining stable thanks to the country's efforts to increase
domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest information from the Shanghai East
China Iron and Steel Market, price of various kinds of threading
steel products has been maintained at about 2,150 yuan per ton.
</P>
<P>
The price for high-quality products from the Shanghai Iron and
Steel Plant has been kept at between 2,160 yuan and 2,170 yuan per
ton.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that the vicious price competition in this
sector, which has persisted for a long time, has been basically
contained, said insiders.
</P>
<P>
However, the price-rise margin will not be too great because it
will take a relatively long time to form a healthy iron and steel
market system, according to experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
