<HEADLINE> International Jewelry Show Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A four-day International
Jewelry Show was opened at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center Monday, attracting a total of 788 exhibitors from 24
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits on display are all kinds of fine jewelry and gems and
related products such as diamond jewelry, colored gemstones,
carvings and display ornaments, pearl jewelry, fresh water pearls
as well as high quality and jewelry watches.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of the show, Leung Sik Wah,
chairman of the Trade Development Council's Jewelry Advisory
Committee, said there are grounds for optimism for Hong Kong's
jewelry exports this year.
</P>
<P>
The United States and European markets, which account for
nearly 70 percent of Hong Kong's total jewelry exports, continue
to show signs of growth.
</P>
<P>
As one of the largest exporters of precious jewelry in the
world, Hong Kong exported more than 10 billion HK dollars (1.28
billion U.S. dollars) worth of precious jewelry worldwide last
year, slightly more than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate the exchange of market information and network
for both exhibitors and buyers, four seminars on the latest
development in the jewelry industry worldwide are being held
during the first three days' show.  
