<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 36 Changes Made to Government Work Report (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A total of 36 changes were made
to Premier Zhu Rongji's government work report which was adopted
at the Second Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC)
, the country's highest legislature, which ended here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The changes were made according to the opinions and suggestions
put forward by the deputies to the NPC session in their
deliberations of the report, and the proposals by members of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference who attended the NPC session as non-voting
observers.
</P>
<P>
Following are the major changes made:
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the great victories achieved in fighting last
summer's devastating flooding in the first part of the government
work report, "in particular, the people's army displayed a crucial
and irreplaceable role" was added.
</P>
<P>
Touching on the rational fund investment in the second part of
the report, the wording "due emphasis on the central and western
regions" was changed into "attention should be paid to giving due
emphasis on the central and western regions, and promote the
economic growth of the central and western regions."
</P>
<P>
On reducing farmers' burden and maintaining stability in rural
areas in the third part of the report, "educate farmers to perform
their due obligations according to law" was added.
</P>
<P>
Talking about ways and means to revitalize small state
enterprises in the fourth paragraph of the report, the following
was added: "selling of small state firms, if deemed necessary,
should be conducted in accordance with relevant state regulations,
" and "supporting medium-sized and small state firms, especially
the science and technology firms with market prospects by
providing them with credit loans, technology, information and
professional training."
</P>
</TEXT>
