<HEADLINE> 30 Injured in KAL Flight Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Thirty people were injured when a
Korean Air Line (KAL) flight with 140 passengers and crew aboard
strayed from runway due to poor weather while landing at Pohang
Airport in North Kyongsang province, South Korea, around 12 a.m.
Monday.
</P>
