<HEADLINE> 36 Changes Made to Government Work Report (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The last paragraph of the fourth part was revised as the
following:
</P>
<P>
"While promoting the reform of state enterprises, big efforts
should be made to develop diversified forms of collective economy
in urban and rural areas while continuously consolidating the
dominating position of the public ownership.
</P>
<P>
"Active efforts should be made to work out policies and
measures to encourage, support and guide the healthy development
of non-public economies including self-employed and private
businesses, to give full play to their role in meeting people's
diversified needs, increasing employment and promoting the growth
of the national economy."
</P>
<P>
In the part about attracting overseas funds in the sixth part
of the report, "continuous efforts should be made to run well the
special economic zones (SEZ) and the Pudong New Areas in Shanghai"
was added.
</P>
<P>
In the part about "implementing the strategy of invigorating
the nation through science and education and the strategy of
sustainable development", the following were added: "intensify the
efforts to absorb and assimilate, improve and upgrade the imported
technology;" "pay attention to training the spirit of innovation
and capability to do practical work;" "continue to improve
teachers' working and living conditions;" "encourage hygienic
production;" "do a good job of running the China '99 International
Horticultural Exposition;" and grasp the two tasks of developing
material production and promoting cultural and ethic progress at
the same time and put equal stress on both and make great efforts
to promote the socialist cultural and ethic progress.
</P>
<P>
Following the wording "further doing a good job of the affairs
concerning overseas Chinese" in the eighth part of the report, "
bring into full play the role of overseas Chinese in promoting the
reform and opening up of the motherland and in realizing its great
cause of peaceful reunification" was added.
</P>
<P>
"Attention should be paid to strengthen national defense
education" was added to the part on modernization construction of
the national defense. 
</P>
</TEXT>
