<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislature Adopts Constitutional Amendment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Second Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature, today
adopted by voting an amendment to the country's Constitution.
</P>
<P>
In a speech delivered at the session's closing meeting here
this afternoon, Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee,
said that the constitutional amendment has been made at an
appropriate time and in accordance with the guidelines of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China held in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The amendment confirms Deng Xiaoping Theory as a guiding
ideology for China's reform and opening up, enshrines the
principle of "governing the country according to law," defines the
country's basic economic and distribution systems in the current
stage and highlights the important role of the non-public sector
of the economy, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
"The amendment, which is needed for further promoting our
country's economic and social development, reflects the successful
practice of reform and opening up and represents the common
aspirations of the people of all ethnic groups across the country,
" he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The top legislator went on to say that the constitutional
amendment has a great bearing on the Chinese people's efforts to
hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, adhere to the
Party's basic line in the primary stage of socialism, develop a
socialist market economy, promote socialist democracy and achieve
socialist ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
"After the amendment, China's Constitution is closer to
perfection and more suitable to the country's actual conditions,
and will play a more significant role in our efforts to forge
ahead triumphantly along the road of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics," Li said.
</P>
<P>
The current amendment is the third of its kind to China's
existing Constitution which was passed in 1982. The previous two
amendments were made in 1988 and 1993, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese legislature is expected to publish the full text of
the constitutional amendment today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
