<HEADLINE> Iran Denounces Israeli Claim over Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Hamid Reza Asefi has harshly condemned Israeli cabinet's
resolution on Israel's claimed sovereignty over a united Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In a quick reaction to the Israeli move, Asefi called the
resolution "without the slightest sense of any commitments to
international norms and laws," according to the official Islamic
Republic News Agency Monday.
</P>
<P>
The agency reported that the spokesman on Sunday evening called
on the world community and Islamic nations to counter such "evil
expansionist designs" of Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet on Sunday adopted a resolution on
Jerusalem, rejecting any division of the city and reconfirming it
as Israeli's permanent capital.
</P>
<P>
The resolution came after the European Union announced not to
recognize Israel's sovereignty over the entire Jerusalem, noting
that its fate will be decided in the final-status talks stipulated
under the 1993 Oslo accords.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also voiced concerns of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference, which is currently chaired by Iran, over
Israel's "dangerous decision and domineering policies" on
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He also blamed the international communities for its
"indecisiveness" over Israel's expansionist policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
