<HEADLINE> Malaysian, S. African Oil Firms to Explore Cooperation Chances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Petronas, Malaysia's
national oil corporation, and Sasol Limited, a South African oil
company, signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU) here Monday,
seeking to explore opportunities between themselves.
</P>
<P>
The MOU was signed with the main objective to fully exploit the
existing and potential synergy between Petronas' wholly-owned
subsidiary Engen Limited and Sasol's certain subsidiaries,
Petronas said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The MOU allows the companies to further define opportunities
for future cooperation and realization of synergy and to enter
into talks to formalize commercial arrangements as they are
identified, it said.
</P>
<P>
There is a substantial potential benefit of consolidation of
the activities of the two companies, it said.
</P>
<P>
The MOU spelt out specific provision for the parties to
facilitate the participation "of a meaningful consolidated black
shareholding in the enlarged entity," Petronas said.
</P>
<P>
Sasol Oil (Pty) Ltd has facilitated the establishment of an oil
company controlled by black shareholders and trading as Excel, it
said. 
</P>
