on the organizing committee and, if that's the case, I think it's
probably best for all if he does that," Carr was quoted in an
interview with Australia's Channel Seven television network.
</P>
<P>
Coles resigned on Friday from his post as international
relations director for the Australian Olympic Committee. But his
IOC member status makes him still entitled to sit on the SOCOG
board.
</P>
<P>
A former Olympic canoeist, Coles has also been urged to resign
by the state's Olympics minister and SOCOG president Michael
Knight, and has been severely criticized by Kevan Gosper, another
Australian IOC member.
</P>
<P>
The SOCOG board was expected to discuss Coles's future at
Monday's meeting in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Coles stood aside temporarily from the SOCOG board and was not
due to attend the Sydney meeting. 
