<HEADLINE> Kidd's Triple-double Inspires Suns to Beat Rockets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Jason Kidd scored his fifth
triple-double of the season to lead the Phoenix Suns to a 104-90
victory over the Houston Rockets in the National Basketball
Association matches on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kidd contributed 26 points, 11 rebounds and 14 assists as the
Suns snapped its four-game home losing streak and avoided falling
under .500.
</P>
<P>
Tom Gugliotta added 17 points and 10 rebounds and Danny Manning,
substitute for injured center Luc Longley, had 15 points for
Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
Former Sun Charles Barkley had 21 points and 12 rebounds and
Hakeem Olajuwon added 17 and 13 for the Rockets.
</P>
<P>
In Sacramento, rookie Jason Williams scored 21 points as the
Kings posted a 105-101 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers, who
saw their 10-game winning streak halted.
</P>
<P>
Chris Webber recorded his 20th double-double of the season with
19 points and 11 rebounds for the Kings.
</P>
<P>
Shaquille O'Neal scored 33 points and Kobe Bryant had 29 for
the Lakers, who played without Dennis Rodman after the
controversial rebounding king asked for a leave of absence.
</P>
<P>
At Detroit, Steve Smith scored 22 points and Mookie Blaylock
had 18 more to lead the Atlanta Hawks to beat the Pistons 85-72.
</P>
<P>
In Miami, Alonzo Mourning registered 25 points and 11 rebounds
and Tim Hardaway had 20 and eight assists to lead the Heat to a
102-76 rout of the hapless New Jersey Nets.
</P>
<P>
At Indiana, Rik Smits scored 14 of his 28 points in the fourth
quarter as the Pacers came from behind to obtain a 99-96 win over
the Boston Celtics.
</P>
<P>
In New York, Larry Johnson scored 13 of his 19 points in the
second half to lead the Knicks to a 94-86 win over the Charlotte
Hornets.
</P>
<P>
In Seattle, Gary Payton scored 28 points and 11 assists as the
Los Angeles Clippers started another losing streak in a 108-89
defeat by the Super Sonics. 
</P>
