<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Taps Vast Natural Gas Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China has prioritized the
development of vast gas reserves in its central and western parts
and has so far built three large natural gas production bases in
the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region, the Tarim Basin, and Sichuan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The central part of the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region has proven
gas reserves of 230 billion cu.m., according to a senior official
with the China National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC). He noted
that new gas-bearing structures are constantly being discovered.
</P>
<P>
The eastern part of Sichuan Province in southwest China has
total verified gas reserves of 200 billion cu.m. while natural gas
reserves in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region total 160 billion
cu. m.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a large gas field in the Sebei area in northwest
China's Qinghai Province has verified reserves of 50 billion cu.m.
</P>
<P>
The official said China plans to double its gas production
capacity to 30 billion cu.m. by the year 2005, the bulk of which
will come from the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia region, Sichuan Province
and Xinjiang.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea Claims Downing Ethiopian Jet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ASMARA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Eritrean defense forces have
shot down one Ethiopian Mig-23 jet fighter, state radio said
Monday, quoting a press release issued by the Eritrean Ministry of
Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's "large-scale offensive on the Tsorona flank of the
central Alitena-mereb front has been repulsed with the enemy
suffering heavy human losses", Dimsti Hafash (Voice of the Masses)
further said.
</P>
<P>
The release issued in Asmara late Sunday said that one Mig-23
jet fighter was shot down and 19 tanks were destroyed while two
others were captured.
</P>
<P>
But Eritrea did not give the number of the human loss on either
side.
</P>
<P>
The release noted that the Ethiopian infantry and mechanized
attacks were accompanied by heavy shellings and air bombardment
with mercenary pilots.
</P>
<P>
It accused Ethiopia of launching "its war of aggression" in
defiance of the United Nations Security Council calls on March 4
urging Ethiopia to stop its continued military action.
</P>
<P>
In Addis Ababa, the office of the Ethiopian government
spokesperson announced Sunday night "there was fighting today on
the Zalambessa-Egela front" between the Ethiopian defense forces
and the Eritrean army.
</P>
<P>
The front is located at eastern Tigray region. Ethiopia accused
Eritrean troops of occupying the border town Zalambessa on June 9
last year.
</P>
<P>
However, an official in the office of the Ethiopian
government spokesperson, Haile Kiros, said there were just
cross-border artillery shellings at Tsorona and other fronts.
</P>
<P>
Fighting had died down since February 27 when Eritrea accepted
the framework agreement put forward by the Organization of African
Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
Only occasional border skirmishes and cross-border shellings
occur on the Badme and Zalambessa front, some 30 kilometers to the
east of Tsorona, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990315.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB to Prepare Micro-Finance Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, march 15 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
announced here Monday that it has approved a regional technical
assistance grant of 400,000 U.S. dollars to prepare a
micro-finance strategy.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the Manila-based bank said that
micro-finance -- providing the poor with loans, savings facilities
and other financial services such as insurance -- is recognized as
a powerful tool for poverty reduction and has been particularly
successful in countries such as Bangladesh and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
However, it said, despite the rapid growth in micro-finance
services in the region, an estimated less than 5 percent of poor
households in the Asia and Pacific region have access to formal
financial services.
</P>
<P>
The ADB's strategy will include expanding access of the poor to
such services, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
An ADB task force on micro-finance will carry out in-country
consultations in several bank's developing members, it said.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that other activities under the technical
assistance will include a regional workshop in Manila to obtain
further inputs for the strategy and a study of the role of central
banks in micro-finance development.
</P>
<P>
The consultations and the study will cover 12 ADB members:
Bangladesh, China, the Philippines, India, Indonesia, Kyrgyz
Republic, Nepal, Pakistan, Papua New Guinea, Sri Lanka, Vanuatu
and Vietnam, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
