<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netherlands Dominate at Speedskating Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Dutchman Bob de Jong outsprinted
his countryman and three-time champion Gianni Romme to take the 10,
000 meters title on Sunday in the Single Distance Speedskating
World Championships at Heerenveen, Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
De Jong's victory wrapped up a remarkable championships for the
hosts, who took five out of the 10 gold medals including four of
the five men's.
</P>
<P>
De Jong finished in 13 minutes 26.61 seconds, well ahead of
Romme who clocked 13:29.83. Germany's Frank Dittrich was third in
13:30.22.
</P>
<P>
In the 1,000m event, Dutchman Jan Bos grabbed victory in 1:10.
41, with Japanese Hiroyasu Shimizu coming second in 1:10.75.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 1500m race, Austrian veteran Emese Hunyady
finished first in 1:58.29, beating her old rival Niemann-
Stirnemann of Germany into second on 1:58.43. 
</P>
