<HEADLINE> hke031517 - 7 Drowned in Ferry Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were drowned
and many others went missing as a boat capsized in Bangladesh
Sunday, press reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
So far, seven bodies have been recovered from the mechanized
boat, which weighed down into Madhumati river in Perojpur
district, 148 kilometers southwest of here, police and witnesses
said.
</P>
<P>
The boat with about 150 passengers aboard sank off Chadkhati
while sailing towards Faridpur district, 112 kilometers northwest
of here, according to local district officials.
</P>
<P>
The boat went down in the middle of the river shortly after
setting sails from Khejurtola terminal in Perojpur district,
police quoted survivors as saying.
</P>
<P>
Villagers and police rushed into rescue and tugged the sunken
boat to the riverbank, and they late retrieved seven bodies
including three of women and two of children from inside the hull
of the foundered boat.
</P>
<P>
The rescue work is still going on, and the cause of the
accident is under investigation, police said. 
