between June and August, according to Wu Jinyou, secretary-general
of the State South Pole Expedition Office.
</P>
<P>
The State Council has approved plans for the expedition which
involve a large number of experts from the agricultural, aquatic
resources, environmental protection, education and meteorological
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The ship used for previous expeditions to the South Pole has a
capacity of only 130 passengers and will be refitted to carry more
scientists on the North Pole.
</P>
<P>
Six Chinese scientists joined an American expedition to the
North Pole in 1995. Non-government funding enabled the Chinese
scientists to conduct extensive oceanographic, ice and snow,
atmospheric and environmental studies along the way.  
