<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets to Improve Housing Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Minister of Construction
Song Chunhua recently called on the construction industry to
introduce measures to solve problems related to substandard
quality within four years.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey revealed substandard levels for approximately
10 percent of residential houses built in major cities during 1998,
down significantly on the 40 percent level in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of Chinese citizens have voiced
dissatisfaction with the poor quality of their houses, said Song.
</P>
<P>
Statistics provided by the China National Consumers Association
show that the number of complaints nationwide concerning defective
houses rose by 50 percent in 1998 from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Song attributed the rising complaints to the fact that
construction companies lack adequate expertise to determine
project quality. He urged related government departments at all
levels to strengthen inspections of construction projects to
ensure quality and consolidate the existing disorderly
construction market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
