The new rules bar drivers from talking over mobile phones or
tuning in radio programs while driving. Violators will be charged
200,000-400,000 Lei ( 14.8-19.5 U.S. dollars) as punishment.
</P>
<P>
Drivers and passengers in the front seat who do not fasten seat
belt will pay a fine of 250,000 lei (about 18.5 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Those who break speed limits will be charged with a fine of 200,
000-400,000 Lei, and serious offenders will also have their
licenses suspended or revoked.
</P>
<P>
There are nearly 2.5 million private cars in the country, or
one for every household.
</P>
<P>
As road development has been lagging behind, road accidents
have been on the rise, causing thousands of deaths or injuries a
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
