<HEADLINE> Problems Affect Consumer Safety, Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey revealed that
problems related to various commodities either threaten or
otherwise harm the personal safety and health of Chinese consumers.
</P>
<P>
The survey conducted by the China Consumers Association also
indicated that Chinese consumers consider safety a primary factor
when selecting commodities. However, the vast majority of Chinese
consumers are unfamiliar with laws and regulations concerning the
safety of commodities and methods for filing compensation claims.
</P>
<P>
Respondents listed major safety problems for gas water heaters,
cigarettes, bottle beer, pressure cookers and medicines.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they demanded the enactment of laws and regulations
governing the safety of housing construction, foodstuffs, refunds,
after-sales services, standards for medical care and medical
accidents.
</P>
<P>
Respondents cited their belief that government, social
organizations and the media can help solve problems related to
product quality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
