<HEADLINE> Albania Urges Kosovo Albanians to Sign Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian government on Sunday
urged the delegation of Kosovo Albanians to sign a peace agreement
with Yugoslavia in the second round of peace talks in France.
</P>
<P>
The government said in a statement that signing an agreement is
a historic action that will eventually open a road to the full
realization of the legitimate national rights of the Kosovo
Albanians.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, the government added, the Albanian government
urges the delegation of Kosovo Albanians to sign the agreement
within the time limit.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government said that by so doing the Kosovo
Albanians will win, instead of being defeated, in face of the
historic challenge at the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
The second round of the Kosovo peace talks, sponsored by the
six-nation Contact Group, is expected to start in Rambouillet,
western suburb of Paris on Monday. The Kosovo Albanians are yet to
reach consensus on whether to sign the peace agreement with the
Yugoslav delegation. 
