<HEADLINE> China to Adopt First Meteorological Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to adopt its
first meteorological law by the end of this year or early next
year.
</P>
<P>
An official with China Meteorological Administration said the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) and the
State Council's Legislative Office are currently soliciting
opinions from various departments, provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions as well as research organizations.
</P>
<P>
He said the meteorological law will cover preparedness against
possible natural disasters and reducing losses from related events,
as well as the development and protection of meteorological
resources and administrative regulations.
</P>
<P>
The draft law, which was amended for 16 times over the past two
years, has been submitted to the State Council for approval.
</P>
<P>
The existing "Meteorological Regulations" in the sphere of
China's Meteorology were adopted in 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
