<HEADLINE> Volkswagen to Double Capacity in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 13 (Xinhua) -- German car-maker Volkswagenwerk AG
will double its production capacity in China even though Asia has
been hit by financial crisis, a senior company official said here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a speech published in Welt am Sonntag, Robert Buechelhofer,
Volkswagenwerk AG's marketing director, said that his company
produced and sold 300,000 units for the first time in 1998,
accounting for 54 percent of China's auto market.
</P>
<P>
He said that his company will raise its production capacity in
China to 600,000 units. He predicted that auto production across
China will increase to about one million units in the coming five
to seven years.
</P>
<P>
Volkswagenwerk announced not long ago that its global market
share this year will rise to 12 percent from 11.5 percent and that
15 percent of the company's production will be sold to the Asia-
Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
While continuing to develop and produce popular energy-saving
models, he said, the company has also been successful in
developing luxury cars in order to meet the needs of the customers
at all levels. The Lupo model, the first in the world to consume
three liters of gasoline per 100 kilometers, will appear in the
market in the first half of this year. 
</P>
