clinch the gold, with his teammate Kasuyoshi Funaki finishing
third, on 241.4 points with jumps of 117.5 and 115.5 meters.
</P>
<P>
Martin Schmitt of Germany took the silver, scoring 245.0 points
on jumps of 114 and 123.5 meters.
</P>
<P>
Finland's Janne Ahonen leads the World Cup standings with 1,589
points. He placed fifth at Holmenkollen with 239.0 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
