<HEADLINE> Increasing Road Construction In East Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- There are roads now to all
townships and villages in China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The province spent more than 800 million yuan last year
building and improving more than 3,000 kilometers of roads to make
13 towns that have been left behind more accessible.
</P>
<P>
There are 16,888 km of roads in Henan that reach poverty-
stricken areas. The improved transport conditions will give a push
to economic development of 34 poverty-stricken counties in the
province, authorities say. 
</P>
