<HEADLINE> China Telecom Provides Government with Access to Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom will introduce a
series of measures and preferential policies to assist government
institutions in setting up their own websites.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom, the largest information network operator in
China, has set up a unified nationwide network platform of public
data and multi-media communications, and the ATM broad band
network platform linking all provincial capitals is also expected
to be completed soon, Shanghai-based Wenhui Daily says today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China Telecom also provides services linking to the
163 net and 169 net access, on which a large number of personal
and enterprises' websites have been established.
</P>
<P>
The preferential policies promised by China Telecom include
providing a 128 k special data line to 163 and 169 nets to each
central government department that contracts with China Telecom to
get hooked up in Internet.
</P>
<P>
It will also provide each provincial-level government
department with a 64 k special data line to 163 and 169 nets.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, China Telecom will provide consultation,
personnel training and other necessary services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
