<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Reports Foreign Exchange Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Banks in south China's
Guangdong Province, one of the nation's major foreign trade
powerhouses, has reported a foreign exchange surplus for the first
two months of this year in spite of the adverse impact of the
Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The 372 million US dollars surplus marked a dramactic reversal
in the depressed foreign exchange level since September last year.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Guangdong Branch of the People's Bank of
China noted the surplus was achieved by overcoming difficulties
resulting from the lingering impact of the financial crisis
engulfing Asia.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the achievement to the financial department's
efforts to strengthen penalties for individuals or enterprises
engaged in fraudulent foreign exchange deals and the emphasis
placed on stimulating export initiatives. 
</P>
