<HEADLINE> Renovating Garden in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Wuxi, in east China's Jiangsu
Province, will spend 10.5 million yuan on the Jichang Garden, one
of the most famous cultural relics south of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The garden was built during the Zhengde period of the Ming
Dynasty, from 1506 to 1522, and is the city's only state-level
cultural relic.
</P>
<P>
Although it has been renovated several times since the
establishment of New China in 1949, it had not retained its
original appearance.
</P>
<P>
So, during the current renovation, major scenic spots in the
garden will be repaired and some people living in the garden will
be relocated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
