<HEADLINE> Increasing Overseas Investment In Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Qingdao in
east China's Shandong added 80 overseas-funded enterprises in the
first two months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Their project contracts were worth 226 million US dollars. The
investments from Asia, Europe and the United States were
respectively 7.8 times, 14.2 times and 14.7 times the figure for
the same 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
Investment in real estate has been under control and went down
99 percent from the same two-month 1998 period. 
</P>
