<HEADLINE> Bank Supports China's Hi-Tech Industrial Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing City Commercial Bank
recently signed a contract with the Beijing Municipal Science and
Technology Commission to provide no less than a billion yuan (120
million U.S. dollars) every year for the city's key hi-tech
projects.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used to put hi-tech developments of
scientific research facilities to industrial use. Officials say
that increasing hi-tech industrial development is the core of the
city's economic restructuring and a lot has been achieved in
investment and funding.
</P>
<P>
An investment and fund-raising system has been set up with
three technology investment companies and three guarantee funds
with more than a billion yuan in capital.
</P>
<P>
The China Agricultural Bank's Beijing Branch also provided 500
million yuan for hi-tech industries at the end of January and the
Industrial and Commercial Bank's Beijing Branch and Construction
Bank's Beijing Branch are also expected to increase support for
major technology enterprises to improve the financial environment
for hi-tech industrial development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
