<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: Exports to Major Partners in First Two Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts
and figures about China's exports to its major trade partners in
the first two months of 1999, provided by the General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Asia reached 11.48 billion U.S. dollars, down 17.
7 percent. Exports to Hong Kong plummeted by 36.8 percent to 3.75
billion U.S. dollars. Exports to Japan and ASEAN went down by 6.7
percent and 6.9 percent to 3.78 billion U.S. dollars and 1.43
billion U.S. dollars, respectively. However, exports to Taiwan and
the Republic of Korea amounted to 480 million U.S. dollars and 930
million U.S. dollars, up 1.7 percent and 7.2 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Africa increased 3.9 percent to 490 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Europe declined by 9.1 percent to 4.3 billion U.S.
dollars. Exports to the European Union went down by 6.1 percent to
3.74 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Latin America dropped 16.7 percent to 570 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to Oceania rose 4.4 percent to 390 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Exports to North America went up 7 percent to 5.17 billion U.
S. dollars. Exports to the United States grew 6.2 percent to 4.85
billion U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
