<HEADLINE> Dutchman Boogerd Wins Paris-Nice Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Michael Boogerd won the first Paris-
Nice cycling race by a Dutchman since Joop Zoetemelk's third
success in 1979 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Rabobank rider finished almost one minute ahead of his
Swiss teammate Markus Zberg, with Colombian Santiago Botero coming
on third.
</P>
<P>
Belgian Tom Steels of Mapei won the 157 km final stage, with
Austrian Harald Morscher and Glenn Magnusson of Sweden for the
second and third places respectively after a final sprint.
</P>
