<HEADLINE> Gunmen Wound Six in Dublin Football Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Six people were wounded on Sunday
in a shooting at a football match in the Irish Republic, reports
from Dublin said.
</P>
<P>
Two masked men drove a motorbike to the football pitch at
Clondalkin, near Dublin, and opened fire on players and spectators,
according to police.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen left five players and a spectator wounded before
fleeing the pitch. All the six injured were taken to hospital.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Irish Garda (police) in Dublin said: "The
injuries are not serious. They are not life-threatening."
</P>
<P>
Police said they knew of no motive for the attack and had no
suspects. They believed the weapon used was a shotgun, the
spokesman said. 
</P>
