<HEADLINE> African Soccer Champions Upset in Gabon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- African soccer champions
ASECG of Cote d'lvoire suffered a 1-0 defeat by Gabonese military
club FC 105 in a first round first leg match of the African
Champions League in Libreville on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The only goal was scored by Gabon's national team defender
Tristan Mombo after 17 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Beaten 1998 finalists Dynamos of Zimbabwe scored three second-
half goals to achieve a surprisingly easy 3-0 victory over Defence
Force in the tiny Southern Africa mountain kingdom of Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
Another military team to succeed were USFA of Burkina Faso, who
overcame Al-Harrach of Algeria 2-0 in Ougadougou through goals by
Urbain Som and Lazare Sanou.
</P>
<P>
Rayon Sport of Rwanda edged AFC Leopards of Kenya 2-1 in an
East African showdown with Paty scoring a 65th-minute winner in
Kigali from a penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
A fifth-minue goal from Tenema Ndiaye and another from Daouda
Diakite soon after the half-time earned Djoliba of Mali an
unexpected 2-0 home victory over Cotonsport Garoua from Cameroon.
</P>
<P>
In the Cup Winnners' Cup, former holders Power Dynamos of
Zambia gave a 6-1 drubbing to Saint Michel United of Seychelles in
the central mining town of Kitwe.
</P>
<P>
In the CAF Cup, Al-Ahly Benghazi of Libya obtained a surprise 1-
1 tie with Wydad Casablanca of Morocco. 
</P>
</TEXT>
