<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Leaves for Visit to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun
Sen left here Monday morning, beginning his two-day official visit
to Indonesia at the invitation of Indonesian President B J
Habibie.
</P>
<P>
The trip is Hun Sen's fifth official visit abroad since
becoming sole prime minister in November. Since December, Hun Sen
has already visited Vietnam, Malaysia, China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen will meet with Habibie and other government leaders in
Indonesia. The two side will also sign an agreement on investment
protection between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the visit, Cambodian government said, is to
strengthen and develop a friendly relationship as well as economic
and trade cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The entourage of the prime minister includes Minister of
Council of Ministers Sok An and other officials.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen is scheduled to return to Phnom Penh on March 17.
</P>
</TEXT>
