<HEADLINE> China Wins Women's Singles at All England Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, March 14 (Xinhua) -- World champion Ye Zhaoying of
China won the women's singles title for the third time in a row
with a win over her teammate Dai Yun at the All England Open
Badminton Championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ye, joint third seed with Dai at the centenary tournament,
rallied from first set down to beat Dai 9-11, 11-5 and 11-1 in an
all-Chinese final.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles final, world number one Peter Gade
Christensen of Denmark battled to his first All England title with
a 15-11, 7-15, 15-10 victory over Indonesian teenager Taufik
Hidayat.
</P>
<P>
The experienced Dane had to fight all the way against his 17-
year-old opponent, the youngest finalist in the men's singles
since 1958.
</P>
<P>
Simon Archer and Jo Goode became local heroes when they took
the mixed crown by defeating South Korea's Ha Tae-kwan and Chung
Jae-hee 15-2, 15-13. It is the first gold for England since 1994
when Nick Ponting and Joanne Wright won the mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
The men's doubles title went to Indonesia's Tony Gunawan and
Candra Wijaya who beat South Koreans Lee Dong-soo and Yoo Yong-
sung 15-7, 15-5.
</P>
<P>
The women's doubles final was won by South Korea's Chung Jae-
hee and Ra Kyung-min. They defeated China's Huang Sui and Lu Ying
15-6, 15-8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
