<HEADLINE> Taliban Welcome UN Decision to Send back Workers to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban have
welcomed the U.N. decision to send back its workers to Afghanistan
terming it a good step conforming with the ground realities in the
war-ravaged country.
</P>
<P>
"This is a good step and we welcome it. We are pleased over it.
We respect the U.N. decision and hope that other such realities
would also be kept in view and they would continue their
services", the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) quoted senior
Taliban official for information and culture Amir Khan Muttaqi as
saying Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Muttaqi said that the Taliban have constituted special security
committees to guarantee the protection of the U.N. workers in
major Afghan cities.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. withdrew its aid workers from Afghanistan in last
August following the killing of an Italian U.N. military observer
in Kabul. 
</P>
